Diagnosis
. Recognized by the following combination of characters: body small; preocular part of head with large, dark brown patch (
Fig. 4
); antennal segment I dark red; pronotum dark brown with three longitudinal, broad, yellow stripes; hemelytron pale brown with yellow and reddish areas (
Fig. 4
); endosoma simple with single sclerite (
Fig. 45
); bursa copulatrix with unpaired sclerotized ring, encircling bursa copulatrix; sclerotization of ventral wall of bursa copulatrix narrow (
Figs 57, 58
).
